Enum Constant Detail

ANTISYMMETRIC_EXTENSION

public static final DataBoundary ANTISYMMETRIC_EXTENSION
This flag indicates that the data are implicitely extended on the left and right borders with two antisymmetric mirrors located exactly on top of the first sample and last samples. For example, if the data to be convolved have the 6 values {-2, 3, 1, 4, 8, 2}, then the implicit extension would be {…, -10, -5, -7, -4, 0, -6, -12, -8, -5, -7, -2, 3, 1, 4, 8, 2, -4, 0, 3, 1, 6, 11, 9, 12, 16, 10, …}

Mathematically, the two following conditions always hold true:
data[k] - data[0] = data[0] - data[-k]
and
data[k + data.length - 1] - data[data.length - 1] = data[data.length - 1] - data[data.length - 1 - k].

FINITE_SUPPORT

public static final DataBoundary FINITE_SUPPORT
This flag indicates that the data is implicitely extended on both sides by the value 0.0.

MIRRORS_BETWEEN_SAMPLES

public static final DataBoundary MIRRORS_BETWEEN_SAMPLES
This flag indicates that the data are implicitely extended on the left and right borders with two mirrors located just before the first sample and just after the last one. For example, if the data to be convolved have 6 samples indexed from 0 to 5, then the implicit extension would access the indices …012345543210012345543210012345…

Mathematically, the two following conditions always hold true:
data[k] = data[-1 - k]
and
data[k + data.length] = data[data.length - 1 - k].
This results in periodic data with the even period (2 * data.length).

MIRRORS_ON_SAMPLES

public static final DataBoundary MIRRORS_ON_SAMPLES
This flag indicates that the data are implicitely extended on the left and right borders with two mirrors located exactly on top of the first sample and last samples. For example, if the data to be convolved have 6 samples indexed from 0 to 5, then the implicit extension would access the indices …01234543210123454321012345…

Mathematically, the two following conditions always hold true:
data[k] = data[-k] (even symmetry)
and
data[k + data.length - 1] = data[data.length - 1 - k].
This results in periodic data with the even period (2 * data.length - 2).

PERIODIC

public static final DataBoundary PERIODIC
This flag indicates that the data are implicitely periodized. For example, if the data to be convolved have 6 samples indexed from 0 to 5, then the implicit extension would access the indices …012345012345012345012345012345…

Mathematically, the following condition always holds true:
data[k + data.length] = data[k].
This results in periodic data with the period data.length.

SPREAD_EXTREMAL_VALUES

public static final DataBoundary SPREAD_EXTREMAL_VALUES
This flag indicates that the first data sample is implicitely replicated on the left border, and the last data sample is implicitely replicated on the right border. For example, if the data to be convolved have 6 samples indexed from 0 to 5, then the implicit extension would access the indices …0000000000000123455555555555…
